The paper deals with generating synthetic fingerprints using a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) and stochastic search to maximize the number of impostor matches. This involves image-level processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the vulnerability of fingerprint recognition systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of GANs and stochastic search can be considered as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
